This is the category & indicator selection panel. Click on the star icon to bookmark the selected indicator.
This panel shows the bookmarked indicator. It is the x-axis variable if the scatterplot graph is selected.
Select any indicators from the list to create a composite indicator. Once indicators have been selected their weights can be adjusted.
In this panel you can select the graph type. You can also customize the graph and change the x and y axis values.
Click on any of the colors or values to change the map colors or values ranges.
This panel shows the values represented by symbols of various sizes.
This table displays the data for the currently selected indicator, as well as the bookmarked indicator - if any.
Click on a country to select or deselect it. You can also create a custom region with the selected countries by clicking on the 'select' button.
This panel contains various options to customize the graph and the map, such as colors and text size.
This panel enables you to customize the map colors. Select a 'diverging' color scheme to emphasize both high and low values.
Export the selected indicator either as a map, graph or table.
This panel provides links to publications and animated maps relevant to the selected country.
